    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jc.00261_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <handShift rend="printed"/>
                    <name type="place">AGENTS</name>
                    <name type="place">for all</name>
                    <name type="place">Free Thought Publications</name>
                    <name type="place">in</name>
                    <name type="place">RELIGION, AND POLITICAL</name>
                    <name type="place">Social and Natural Science.</name>
                    <name type="place">CHARLES P. SOMERBY,<ptr target="loc.01933_n1"/></name>
                    <name type="place">Publishers, Booksellers and Importers.</name>
                    <name type="place">36 DEY STREET.</name>
                    <name type="place">New York,</name>
                    <date when="1875-03-16"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Mch. 16. <handShift rend="printed"/>187<handShift rend="manuscript"/>5</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Mr. Whitman,</salute>
                <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>We are in receipt of your letter and regret, exceedingly, that we <unclear reason="deletion" cert="high" resp="#km">are</unclear> 
                unable to remit the amount you name at present. We have been unable to collect, and our statements of last month 
                have failed to bring us in a quarter of what is due. This is only a temporary embarrassment but it places us in 
                an unpleasant position for the time.</p>
            <p>We hope to be able to forward the amount due you soon 
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jc.00262_large.jpg" type="verso"/> 
                and will certainly do so at our earliest <hi rend="underline">possible</hi> oppor<unclear reason="deletion" cert="high" resp="#km">tunity</unclear></p>
            <p>We hope to visit Philadelphia soon and will not fail to call upon you. Hoping that our failure to raise the money will 
                not inconvenience you <unclear reason="deletion" cert="medium" resp="#al">seriously</unclear></p>
            
            <closer>
                <salute>We remain</salute>
                <salute>Yours very Sincerely</salute>
                <signed>C. P. Somerby</signed>
            </closer>

